
[1]chisel

   CHISEL, n. An instrument of iron or steel, used in carpentry, joinery,
   cabinet work, masonry, sculpture, &c., either for paring, hewing or
   gouging. Chisels are of different sizes and shapes, fitted for
   particular uses.

   CHISEL, v.t. To cut, pare, gouge, or engrave with a chisel.
